fern
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:as simplex, or as common fern applied to a plant of open spaces, usu. <i>Pteridium esculentum</i>, =bracken; often {?occas.] to <i>Paesia scaberula</i>,  ring fern (q.v. ?2.?. below); occas. to <i>Blechnum spp. </i>. See also bracken, fern-tree, hymenophyllum, lycopodium,  para, polypody, ponga, Prince of Wales feathers,  spleenwort [prob out],  Cf. fire in the fern; land of ferns. See further 1989  Brownsey and Smith-Dodsworth New Zealand Ferns and Allied Plants.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: also tree fern
Pronunciation:
Notes:
